## Workflow Rules

### 1. Before Starting Work
{{#if integrations.linear.enabled}}
- [ ] Ensure Linear issue exists (or create one)
- [ ] Get branch name from Linear issue
{{/if}}
- [ ] Read relevant AGENTS.md files for the areas you'll modify
- [ ] Pull latest changes from `{{integrations.github.default_branch}}`
- [ ] Create feature branch following naming convention

### 2. During Work
- [ ] Follow architecture patterns defined in layer AGENTS.md files
- [ ] Keep commits atomic and well-described
- [ ] Update documentation as you code
- [ ] Add tests for new functionality
- [ ] Run linting and formatting before committing

### 3. After Completing Work
{{#if integrations.linear.enabled}}
- [ ] Update Linear issue status
- [ ] Link PR to Linear issue
{{/if}}
- [ ] Create PR against `{{integrations.github.default_branch}}`
- [ ] Ensure all CI checks pass
- [ ] Request code review
- [ ] Update AGENTS.md if architectural patterns changed

